definitions: I LEFT/Ami mbe kuka. - ALONE/esa; LEAVE ME ALONE:/ Ndji esa! - BEHIND/sya.
THE SALT IN THE FOOD BECAME LESS/Omongwa mbwa ri mo-vikurya wa hahuruka.
IS THE SHEEP ALIVE OR IS IT DEAD?/Ondu i no-muinyo poo ya koka?
WORK LIKE THIS!/Ungura nai! WORK ACCORDING TO A GIVEN EXAMPLE/Ungura nao!
STAY IN BED FOR A LITTLE WHILE!/Kara kaţiţi mombete!
I LIVE IN KATUTURA/Mba tura mokatutura.
LOCK WITH A KEY/pata notjipaturure, yezera(e).
EVERY YEAR OUR FAMILY STAYS WITH US/Omuhoko wetu u sekira poyetu ombura aihe.
MY MOTHER IS NOT HERE, I AM LONGING FOR HER/Mama wa i, nambano me hihanwa omutima.

- AT/tarera(e). - INTO/natera (e), munina. - FOR/konga(o), kova (o), paha, pamba-ha, pyanga, tjinga(i). - (SEEK)/yevayeva. - AFTER ONESELF/rita-rera(e). - AROUND/yeva(e). - FIXEDLY (BECAUSE OF BAD SIGHT)/nandinda.
THE HANDCUFFS ARE LOOSE/Ovipandeke vya huhunuka.
- ONE'S WAY/pu-ka. - TASTE OR INTEREST/kuha (u). I AM GOING HOME HAVING LOST ALL INTEREST IN THE GAME/Me yaruka konganda enyando ra kuhu.
WE LOST THE TRACK/twa zengaiza ondambo.
HE SLEEPS ON HIS STOMACH/Wa rara ohomba, ondurumika.
